{
  "texts": [
    "Although our results are promising in terms of the observed intervention effects on loneliness, we cannot rule out the possibility that the intervention changed how service members conceptualized study constructs.",
    "Ideally, we would conduct measurement invariance analyses with our longitudinal data (Somaraju et al., 2022).",
    "The clustered nature of the data, with service members nested within battalions, adds complexity to the statistical approach for analyzing measurement invariance, and results in a multiple group -multilevel structure.",
    "There are unfortunately not clear guidelines on data requirements and procedures for conducting such a test.",
    "However, given the (relatively small) number of groups and number of observations within groups in our overtime data, we had significant concern about the power to reject the null hypothesis that the measures are similar."
  ]
}